'''Ağbulaq''' (also spelled '''Agbulak''', '''Agbulag''', '''Aghboulagh''', {{lang-hy|Ակնաղբյուր ('''Aknakbyur'''}}) is a village in the [[Khojavend Rayon]] of [[Azerbaijan]]. Since the [[Nagorno-Karabakh war]] the town has been administered by the de facto [[Republic of Artsakh]] as part of [[Hadrut Region|Hadrut Province]].<ref>http://census.stat-nkr.am/nkr/1-1.pdf</ref>

