'''Charlestown-Bellahy''' ({{Irish place name|Baile Chathail-Béal Lathaigh}}) is a [[List of census towns in the Republic of Ireland|census town]] split between [[County Mayo]] and [[County Sligo]] in [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]]. It comprises the adjoining villages of [[Charlestown, County Mayo]], and  [[Bellahy]], County Sligo, had a [[population]] of 753 at the 2002 [[census]].
