{{Location map | United States | lat_deg = 27 | lat_dir = N | lon_deg = 94 | lon_dir = W }} [[File:NW GOM features.svg|thumb|Bathymetric features of the northwestern Gulf of Mexico|320px]] '''Keathley Canyon''' is an [[submarine canyon|undersea canyon]] in the [[United States]] [[Exclusive Economic Zone]] in the [[Gulf of Mexico]]. The canyon is named for the hydrographic survey ship [[USNS Sgt. George D Keathley (T-APC-117)|USNS ''Sergeant George D. Keathley'' (T-AGS-35)]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gebco.net/about_us/meetings_and_minutes/documents/gebco_scufn_16_report.pdf |title=Sixteenth Meeting of the GEBCO Sub-committee on Undersea Feature Names (SCUFN) |author=GEBCO Sub-committee on Undersea Feature Names |date=10–12 April 2003 |work= |publisher=International Hydrographic Bureau, Monaco |accessdate=11 February 2012}}</ref>
The Canyon is rich in [[oil field]]s. The major oilfields at the Keathley Canyon are [[Tiber Oil Field|Tiber]],<ref name=subseaiq4> {{cite news | url = http://www.subseaiq.com/data/Project.aspx?project_id=526 | title = Tiber | work = SubSeaIQ | accessdate = 2011-06-09}} </ref> [[Kaskida Oil Field|Kaskida]],<ref name=kaskida> {{cite web | title= Kaskida Field, USA | url= http://www.offshore-technology.com/projects/kaskida-field/ | work=Offshore-Technology | publisher = Net Resources International | accessdate= 2011-06-09}} </ref> Lucius,<ref name=subseaiq2> {{cite news | url = http://www.subseaiq.com/data/Project.aspx?project_id=572 | title = Lucius | work = SubSeaIQ | accessdate = 2011-06-09}} </ref> and Buckskin.<ref name=subseaiq3> {{cite news | url = http://www.subseaiq.com/data/Project.aspx?project_id=467 | title = Buckskin | work = SubSeaIQ | accessdate = 2011-06-09}} </ref> Many oil companies, including [[Chevron Corporation]], [[BP]], [[Anadarko Petroleum]], [[ExxonMobil]], [[Repsol]],<ref>Smith, Thomas, [http://www.geoexpro.com/geoexpro/hot_spot/more-giant/ "More Giant Oil Discoveries"], ''GEO ExPro Magazine'', NO2 - 2010. Retrieved 2011-08-19.</ref> [[Royal Dutch Shell|Shell]], [[Devon Energy]], [[BHP Billiton]], [[Eni]], and [[Total S.A.]] have leased the rights to drill for oil in this area.{{Citation needed|date=August 2011}}
In June, 2011, ExxonMobil announced two major oil and gas discoveries in Keathley Canyon blocks 918, 919, and 964 (Hadrian field)<ref name=subseaiq1> {{cite news | url = http://www.subseaiq.com/data/Project.aspx?project_id=474 | title = Hadrian | work = SubSeaIQ | accessdate = 2011-06-09}} </ref> {{convert|250|mi}} southwest of New Orleans, with combined estimated reserves of {{convert|700|Moilbbl}}.<ref name=offshore080611> {{cite news | url = http://www.offshore-mag.com/index/article-display/9500826399/articles/offshore/drilling-completion/us-gulf-of-mexico/2011/June/exxonmobil-adds_to.html | title = ExxonMobil adds to Keathley Canyon success | newspaper = Offshore Magazine | publisher = [[PennWell Corporation]] | date = 2011-06-08 | accessdate = 2011-06-09}} </ref> The find was "the company’s first deepwater exploration well following a U.S. moratorium" after the [[Deepwater Horizon explosion]] and [[Deepwater Horizon oil spill|oil spill]] in the Gulf in 2010 and "one of the largest discoveries in the Gulf ... in the last decade." "Exxon holds a 50% working interest in four ... blocks. Units owned by [[Petrobras]] and [[Eni]] SPA hold a 25% interest in three of the blocks. Petrobras also owns 50% of one of the blocks."<ref>Gelsi, Steve, [http://www.marketwatch.com/story/exxon-mobil-100-a-barrel-oil-lift-energy-stocks-2011-06-08?dist=afterbell "Exxon holds on to gains, energy stocks fall back"], ''MarketWatch'', June 8, 2011, 4:47 p.m. EDT. Retrieved 2011-06-08.</ref>
{{Geographic location |Center = Keathley Canyon |North = [[Garden Banks]] |Northeast = [[Green Canyon]] |East = [[Walker Ridge]] |Southeast = [[Amery Terrace]] |South = [[Sigsbee Escarpment]] |Southwest = |West = [[Alaminos Canyon]] |Northwest = [[East Breaks]] }}
