{{short description|A prehistoric continent that consisted of mainland and maritime Southeast Asia}} '''Sunda''' was a prehistoric continent that consisted of Mainland and [[Maritime Southeast Asia|Maritime]] [[Southeast Asia]]. It was partially submerged around 18,000 years ago.<ref name="phys">{{cite web|url=https://phys.org/news/2018-04-island-hopping-route-people-australia.html|website=phys.org|title=Island-hopping study shows the most likely route the first people took to Australia|accessdate=2018-08-09}}</ref><ref name="google">{{cite book|title=Prehistory of the Indo-Malaysian Archipelago: Revised Edition|author=Bellwood, P.|date=2007|publisher=ANU E Press|isbn=9781921313127|url=https://books.google.pl/books?id=4obAfGBGKY0C&pg=PA36|page=36|accessdate=2018-08-09}}</ref>
Sahul and Sunda were points of early human migrations after leaving Africa.<ref name="google2">{{cite book|title=Biological Aspects of Human Migration|author1=Mascie-Taylor, D.B.A.C.G.N.|author2=Mascie-Taylor, C.G.N.|author3=Lasker, G.W.|date=1988|publisher=Cambridge University Press|isbn=9780521331098|url=https://books.google.pl/books?id=eJD5XJlviukC&pg=PA18|page=18|accessdate=2018-08-09}}</ref>
